				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$R_0$$\end{document}R0 depends strongly on the socio-spatial distribution of gatherings, but is in fact independent of the duration of infectivity M. Thus we find that for airborne diseases, mitigation by reducing large gatherings will also work well for diseases that do not exhibit heterogeneous spreading (\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
